>excuse the small essay

Records of the experiments and more importantly: the reasons why are few and far between, and really just scraps.
This gave rise to the first generation of anthros in the late 50's and their population blossomed globally from there with... mixed results.
It's really only thanks to an intel leak in 1960 warning the planet of an incoming alien doomsday that kept tensions low enough to avoid an all out race war.
The genius responsible for the creation of a whole new set of species 'The Good Doctor' died after accomplishing his work and didn't really leave anything else behind, he lives on as a cultural vestige of every anthro of every shape, size, and species.
The human view on The Good Doctor and the results of his work is that anthros were created as a breed of supersoldier for the defence of earth, and the man himself isn't around to confirm or deny his intentions.

So far it's really only been a background facet in the story, since ultimately we're here for the characters.
